##Mask machine market chaos: late delivery, spare parts, take the drawings dare to quote

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

"There's no more honesty, only money. "

With the development of the epidemic, manufacturers rushed to join the ranks of mask production.

But it's hard to say it's been smooth sailing. Many enterprises in the conversion before the preconceived underestimated the mask production technology content. As the process progressed, a number of problems came to light. It was discovered that a small mask, involving a lot of parts, raw materials, production equipment and qualification standards, all run through, is not much easier than other products.

Time is short and demand is high. They swarm in, feeling their way across the river. Trouble is almost inevitable.

Dissension

On the evening of February 29, a crowd of people and cars surrounded the gate of wintek's factory.

It's all about the win-win clients. Most of them are new to the industry. They gave a down payment, cleaned the plant, stored the meltblown cloth, and waited for the respirator to arrive. However, near the delivery time, the supplier has delayed again and again, the patience of customers was quickly exhausted. Distraught, they surrounded the win-win technology plant area, trying to "ROB" out some equipment.

According to an earlier report in the Chinese Entrepreneur magazine, wintek's primary business was lithium battery manufacturing equipment. The company has been receiving orders for two hundred masks a day since news broke on Feb. 4 that wintek would urgently produce them, bringing the total to nearly 1,600 as of Feb. 16. At the end of February, about 2,000 units were ordered by wintek, according to industry sources. But the actual output is nowhere near that figure.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the night of February 29th, at the gate of the win-win Technology Factory. Image courtesy of the web

Yu Nan is one of wintek's clients. In February, he ordered eight production lines of face masks for 550,000 yuan each. But I still haven't gotten one.

"there is no more honesty in this industry, only money, " Yu said in an interview with China News weekly, sounding exasperated. "Add a few tens of thousands, and you immediately tear up the contract and sell it to someone else. "

The reasons for the delay in delivery are complex, involving technology reserves, upstream supply chain and many other reasons. Wintek is not alone. Yu's company has also ordered four additional masks from Nuofeng, which has promised to deliver them by March 4, but has also not yet heard from them.

According to a set of data provided by the Shenzhen Medical Association, the mainstream face mask machine on the market has a beat of 6,000 per hour, while the old model has a beat of 3,600-4,000 per hour. But many of those who switch to other products fall far short of that requirement.

Yu told China news weekly that he had been to Shenzhen, a number of mask manufacturers on-site visits. In his view, the smooth operation of the machine is not many, almost all have large and small problems.

"It's either stuck here or stuck there, and there are basically no runners, " Yu told China news weekly. "You're lucky to get hundreds an hour. " "I came from a technical background, and I was working with them to figure out what it would look like if a boss with no technical background bought it back. "

But with the outbreak, everyone is getting impatient. Yu Nan also admitted that this time, has the ability to deliver the whole machine supplier, can already be called "Conscience Enterprise" . Some manufacturers deliver a bunch of parts and tell customers to go back and assemble them themselves; even worse, they just download the drawings on the Internet and claim they can make face masks and start taking deposits.

In addition to the hardware constraints, mask machine installation, commissioning and daily maintenance of the necessary manpower is also quite scarce.

Hu Hui, the regulation manager of the Shenzhen Medical Device Industry Association (hereinafter referred to as "Shenzhen Medical Association") , explained to China News weekly that before the outbreak, taking Shenzhen as an example, there are only four manufacturers, namely Shenzhen Zhonghai Medical Products Co. , Ltd. , innolux technology (Shenzhen) Co. , Ltd. , Shenzhen Yuguan Medical Devices Co. , Ltd. and Shenzhen Tengta Antibacterial Textile Co. , Ltd. , which hold valid registration certificates for medical masks. Yuguan and Teng are not involved in mask production; Innoli is mainly aimed at overseas markets; only Shenzhen Zhonghai has experience in the production and sale of masks in China. As a result, the industry has not built up an adequate staff pool.

Although civilian masks are similar to medical masks in product technology and process, most people can share them, and government departments have coordinated some of the companies that originally produced masks to send staff to temporary cross-border companies to provide technical guidance. But on the whole, the contradiction of lack of technical personnel is still outstanding.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On March 4,2020, workers of Shandong Kangli Medical Equipment Technology Co. , Ltd. of Luhua Group inspected the quality of medical products under strict disinfection environment. China News Service, photo by Jizhe

Hu Hui explained to China News weekly that many business owners were too eager to enter the bureau, thinking that the mask production technology is simple, that is, "three layers of cloth pressed together. ". As a result, things can be made, but they simply can not be produced in large quantities.

"For example, this is a bit like a Philips Razor. It looks like a simple thing, but many details need to be accumulated, which can not be seen on the outside, and can only be understood in practice, " said Hu.

Advice

An estimated 423.2 million masks are needed each day, multiplied by a factor of health workers, students and retirees, according to the public's snowballing the world. According to Huachuang Securities Analysis, China's secondary and tertiary employment population of about 530 million people, assuming each person a day, all back to work, a day needs to consume masks up to 530 million.

Spurred on by demand, capital and companies poured in to try to grab a piece of the Pie. IDEAL IS PLUMP: A mask automatic production line and raw materials, 24 hours a day, at least 100,000 masks. Assuming a profit of RMB1 per mask, the maximum return is five days. After that, you can make as many days as you drive the machine.

But the reality is very skinny. The above-mentioned situation of win-win technology is a direct manifestation of the contradiction.

March 2, Shenzhen Medical Association issued a paper suggesting: Small and medium-sized enterprises should be cautious into the bureau mask production. The article explains that some of the mask automation line manufacturers are currently facing the problem of extended delivery time, the reasons can be summarized as follows:

1. Some mask automation manufacturers did not produce mask production line before the epidemic, is a transfer of production, manufacturing capacity problems;

2. Orders too much, manpower shortage, orders far greater than their own human bearing range;

3. Upstream parts shortage and delay delivery, more typical is the ultrasonic welding machine, headband machine, metal parts, etc. 

4. The government adds the order temporarily, causes the commercial order to delay the delivery;

5. Stoppage phenomenon is serious, for example, Yu Nan mentioned above, "whoever adds money to whom. ". But it's just a theory. There's no proof.

Many of these factors, it is difficult to say can be reversed human results. In particular, the upstream parts supply shortage and government orders, is beyond the control of enterprises. Therefore, Cai Qiaowu, vice president of the Shenzhen Medical Association, is more inclined to understand the dispute from a good direction: "fighting the epidemic with one heart, in fact, we all mean well, but sometimes it is inevitable to overestimate their own strength. "

Cai Qiaowu thinks, supplier defaults already be the fact that is incontestable. Pointing fingers, blocking doors, or even fighting each other is not going to solve the problem. It's a lose-lose situation. "We do not agree with the supplier's approach, but to solve the problem, both sides should sit down and find a mutually acceptable solution. "

From a macro point of view, the transfer of production enterprises or played a role. On February 24th, as recently as last year, the country produced just 54m masks a day. According to the National Development and Reform Commission, which announced on March 2nd, as of February 29th, the daily production of face masks, including face masks, medical masks and N95 face masks, will reach 110 million and 116 million respectively, doubled in five days.

According to Jiao Yi, Deputy secretary-general of Shenzhen Medical Association, the increase is mainly due to the use of existing meltblown cloth efficiency has been improved. However, there is no effective substitute for meltblown cloth, so only in terms of medical masks, in the short term, the number of further large increase is unlikely. And investment in the production of meltblown cloth required funds are too high, in addition to the national team, small and medium-sized enterprises into the bureau of power is insufficient.

But the national team is also on the move. According to Caijing, the CPC group decided on February 24 to build 10 production lines of meltblown fabrics by taking advantage of its own raw material production. About $200 million. After full production, 12 tons of N95 melt-blown cloth can be produced every day, or 18 tons of raw material for medical flat mask can be produced. If all were used to produce flat masks for medical use, the daily production could reach 18 million.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
March 2,2020, Beijing Yan Mountains Petrochemical New meltblown non-woven fabric production line project site machinery roaring. Recently, Sinopec decided to invest about 200 million yuan in Beijing, Yan Mountains petrochemical and Jiangsu Yizheng Chemical Fiber two enterprises to speed up the construction of melt-blown non-woven cloth (melt-blown cloth) , spunbonded cloth production lines, is expected to start production in early March. China News Service, photo by Hu Qingming

In view of the above factors, Shenzhen Medical Association appeal, small and medium-sized enterprises or should be within their capabilities, not only to conduct a comprehensive assessment of their own capacity, but also to their own development in the industry and positioning. Regardless of their own circumstances into the bureau mask production, is likely to face many unexpected difficulties, and even legal risks, resulting in heavy losses.

In the interview, Hu also referred to the concept of the "Notification Commitment System" : In an epidemic, the government has limited energy and can not, as usual, go through each qualification of the enterprise, therefore, the party concerned shall be informed in writing of the obligation or condition of proof stipulated in the laws and regulations, and the applicant shall undertake in writing that these conditions, standards and requirements have been met, executive branch is also willing to accept the legal liability for false promises, so it will not require proof, but will handle the matter directly.

But if the enterprise in the signing of the commitment, the product was found to be unqualified, it is likely to face product forfeiture, or even 10-20 times the value of the fine.

"We have been in this industry for a long time, in fact, we can see by the state, who is serious about doing technology, who is Disturb the water and catch a fish, " Hu said.

As of press time, Yu Nan also failed to get a mask machine. His Day job has changed from calling for a refund to negotiating with the supplier.

As for the costs that have been spent, such as plant cleaning and personnel training, can only be claimed. Fortunately, meltblown cloth is 200,000 yuan a ton of purchase price, now the market price has risen to about 350,000 a ton, resell out, can return some of the original.

"If you lose, you lose. What can you do? " Yu Nan said.

Yu Nan was given a pseudonym at the request of the interviewee
